eft quadrant (LLQ).","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.13092,0.21153,0.16504,0.10095,0.072106,0.072627,0.05447,0.060565,0.043884,0.034958,0.028426,0.024519],"unified_progress":[0.11362,0.14344,0.11824,0.11109,0.089201,0.088147,0.072018,0.077961,0.063773,0.049398,0.040871,0.032232]},{"section":5,"text":"Hmm, chronic constipation makes me think of possible bowel obstruction or something related to that.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.072895,0.12568,0.14422,0.13488,0.10746,0.081522,0.072699,0.062105,0.053963,0.063472,0.041555,0.039553],"unified_progress":[0.063846,0.088663,0.095431,0.10986,0.10353,0.094587,0.093731,0.083971,0.076485,0.084449,0.059743,0.045702]},{"section":6,"text":"But the key here is the location of the tenderness in the LLQ.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.067598,0.11664,0.12282,0.11726,0.10241,0.088653,0.0793,0.07224,0.065705,0.063646,0.053082,0.050644],"unified_progress":[0.063915,0.084919,0.092961,0.10427,0.09918,0.09405,0.092134,0.088109,0.082228,0.078794,0.065303,0.054139]},{"section":7,"text":"The sigmoid colon is in the left lower quadrant, right?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.051265,0.096903,0.10486,0.107,0.10187,0.097561,0.091348,0.08326,0.082342,0.069782,0.060097,0.053711],"unified_progress":[0.055355,0.078976,0.094958,0.10983,0.1065,0.10109,0.096107,0.089071,0.086917,0.071401,0.058658,0.051132]},{"section":8,"text":"So maybe a sigmoid volvulus?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043125,0.087406,0.10055,0.10524,0.10178,0.097049,0.092926,0.085631,0.084961,0.077494,0.064322,0.059521],"unified_progress":[0.044378,0.074428,0.09241,0.10485,0.10643,0.10291,0.099388,0.09183,0.088783,0.077721,0.063305,0.053571]},{"section":9,"text":"That's when the sigmoid twists on itself, causing an obstruction.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040987,0.081862,0.092041,0.099344,0.10101,0.10029,0.097823,0.090693,0.086944,0.079512,0.067415,0.06208],"unified_progress":[0.04498,0.069468,0.087014,0.099476,0.10224,0.10789,0.1004,0.094789,0.090565,0.079845,0.066691,0.056637]},{"section":10,"text":"It's more common in elderly patients, especially those with a history of constipation.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038596,0.07695,0.086697,0.09366,0.099021,0.10412,0.099319,0.095101,0.087529,0.086622,0.071906,0.060478],"unified_progress":[0.069687,0.094965,0.09197,0.091571,0.091737,0.09751,0.091058,0.09168,0.083654,0.078334,0.065596,0.052238]},{"section":11,"text":"Alternatively, could it be a diverticulitis?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035219,0.073455,0.086844,0.09424,0.098141,0.097797,0.097978,0.095619,0.093872,0.089119,0.075872,0.061843],"unified_progress":[0.043993,0.07611,0.093407,0.10454,0.1026,0.10001,0.099316,0.093807,0.089852,0.082592,0.065454,0.048313]},{"section":12,"text":"Diverticulitis often presents with LLQ pain, but usually there's more of a left-sided colitis.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03281,0.069069,0.081142,0.092394,0.10027,0.10312,0.10447,0.099349,0.091512,0.089047,0.074709,0.062113],"unified_progress":[0.03792,0.064062,0.08387,0.093897,0.1008,0.1099,0.10441,0.10154,0.095229,0.088126,0.06969,0.050571]},{"section":13,"text":"But the patient's history is chronic constipation, which is a risk factor for volvulus.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034584,0.072245,0.083162,0.090161,0.095508,0.10103,0.099593,0.097435,0.092656,0.090373,0.078767,0.064483],"unified_progress":[0.064848,0.086851,0.086616,0.088737,0.0919,0.094598,0.092577,0.093944,0.088855,0.085606,0.07128,0.054187]},{"section":14,"text":"Diverticulitis might have fever or leukocytosis, which isn't mentioned here.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028305,0.063585,0.077046,0.0